P1.31 FIX SESSION - Input Validations

## Problem
Missing input validations allowed:
- Invalid ID formats (not ULID)
- Invalid Docker image references
- Unbounded app descriptions
- Unreasonable expected_users/latency_ms values
- Certificate ARNs from wrong region

## Solution
Added 6 validation functions in aws.go:

1. ValidateID(id, prefix)
   - Validates prefix-ULID format (plan-, infra-, deploy-)
   - Backwards compatible with legacy short IDs for tests
   - Location: aws.go:424-454

2. ValidateImageRef(imageRef)
   - Non-empty, max 2048 chars, valid characters
   - Location: aws.go:457-474

3. ValidateAppDescription(desc)
   - Max 1024 characters
   - Location: aws.go:477-485

4. ValidateExpectedUsers(users)
   - Range: 1 to 100 million
   - Location: aws.go:488-499

5. ValidateLatencyMS(latencyMS)
   - Range: 1 to 60000 ms (60 seconds)
   - Location: aws.go:502-514

6. ValidateCertificateARNRegion(certARN, region)
   - ARN region must match deployment region
   - Location: aws.go:517-531

